title: Apollo 11 - Flight To The Moon
description:
A very rare item, Apollo 11: Flight To The Moon is an audio documentary of the US space program culminating in the first manned expedition to another celestial body.  Narrated by Wally Schirra, this album presents actual voice transmissions of notable moments in the US space program.

Track Listing (Some tracks slightly renamed):

01 America&#039;s First Manned Flight (Alan Shepard)
02 Orbiting The Earth (John Glenn)
03 Reentry Into Earth&#039;s Atmosphere (Scott Carpenter)
04 Walk In Space (Ed White)
05 Rendezvous Above The Earth (Gemini 6 & 7)
06 First Orbiting Of The Moon (Apollo 8)
07 Approaching The Lunar Surface (Apollo 10)
08 To The Moon (Apollo 11)
09 On The Lunar Surface (Apollo 11)
10 Return To Earth (Apollo 11)

To the best of my knowledge, this album was only released on vinyl and 8-track cassette, cassettes not being popular until some years after this album&#039;s release, and CDs not even a twinkle in the eye of their designers.
